<h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>

<p>Both OpenAI and Anthropic offer fine-tuning APIs that let you specialise a foundation model on your own labeled dataset. The cost structures and JSONL formats are different enough that a dataset that validates cleanly for GPT-4.1 will fail validation for Claude — and vice versa. This guide covers exactly what changes.</p>

<p>The short version: OpenAI uses the ChatML format with a top-level <code>messages</code> array. Anthropic uses a similar structure but calls it "Harmony" internally, enforces a strict <code>system</code> message as the first turn, and rejects the <code>name</code> field that OpenAI allows on messages.</p>

