<h2 id="formats">JSONL Formats</h2>

<p>Both use JSONL: one JSON object per line, no trailing commas, UTF-8 encoded. The structural differences are in the object schema.</p>

<h3 id="chatml">ChatML — OpenAI GPT-4.1</h3>

<pre><code>{`{"messages": [
  {"role": "system", "content": "You are a helpful assistant."},
  {"role": "user",   "content": "What is the capital of France?"},
  {"role": "assistant", "content": "Paris."}
]}`}</code></pre>

<p>Rules that catch most validation failures:</p>
<ul>
  <li>The last message must have <code>"role": "assistant"</code>. A dataset that ends on a user turn is rejected.</li>
  <li>Roles must be exactly <code>system</code>, <code>user</code>, or <code>assistant</code>. The string <code>"human"</code> fails.</li>
  <li>The <code>system</code> message is optional, but if present it must be the first message.</li>
  <li>A <code>name</code> field is permitted on messages for multi-agent datasets.</li>
  <li>Minimum 10 examples, maximum 50,000 per training run.</li>
  <li>Maximum 65,536 tokens per example (all messages combined).</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="harmony">Harmony — Anthropic Claude</h3>

<pre><code>{`{"messages": [
  {"role": "system",    "content": "You are a helpful assistant."},
  {"role": "user",      "content": "What is the capital of France?"},
  {"role": "assistant", "content": "Paris."}
]}`}</code></pre>

<p>The format looks identical but the validation rules differ:</p>
<ul>
  <li>A <code>system</code> message is <strong>required</strong> as the first message. Claude's fine-tuning API enforces this; omitting it returns a schema error.</li>
  <li>The <code>name</code> field is not supported. If your OpenAI dataset uses named turns, strip them before converting.</li>
  <li>Roles must be <code>system</code>, <code>user</code>, or <code>assistant</code> — same strings, no others.</li>
  <li>The last message must be <code>assistant</code>.</li>
  <li>Minimum 10 examples.</li>
</ul>

<p>In practice, the cleanest migration path from OpenAI to Claude is: ensure every example has a system turn, remove any <code>name</code> fields, and run the Claude preset validator in DataPrep. Most clean ChatML datasets pass with only those two fixes.</p>

